Suarez on Coutinho: &ldquo;Obviously he must have ambition because he&rsquo;s a player who has ambition and any player would want to come to Barca. He went through a difficult moment but as a professional he continued to show how good a player he is and the personal quality he has.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Su&aacute;rez: &ldquo;Despite trying to leave Liverpool he continued helping the team and working. He is demonstrating as a professional who has the ambition to take a step further.&rdquo;

Ralf Rangnick has confirmed that there is no way Liverpool will sign Naby Keita in January.<br />
<br />
Rangnick: &ldquo;Even if we should not reach the knockout stages of Champions League, it would make no sense to allow Naby to join Liverpool earlier, we want to qualify for Europe again, and we need Naby for that.&rdquo;

Klopp: &ldquo;Why Liverpool? I had an offer of another historical English club two years ago, but I never felt comfortable with how they understood football. It didn&rsquo;t feel right. When Liverpool called, I can&rsquo;t explain it. It was right.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Klopp: &ldquo;The best player I&rsquo;ve ever coached? Mario G&ouml;tze. He was unbelievable. The biggest improvement, though, was Lewandowski.&rdquo;
